    "body": "I think the error message is a bit misleading here.\r\n\r\nYour beacon-chain is listening to 127.0.0.1\r\nRunning docker this is the local interface within the container and not visible to the outside world. Your validator cannot connect to it, even via the 'host' network (which should be avoided anyways).\r\n\r\nWhat you want to do is:\r\n- Create a docker network\r\n`docker network create --attachable medalla`\r\n\r\n- Start beacon-chain, make it listen to all interfaces and attach it to the docker network\r\n`docker run --name beacon-chain --network medalla -v e:/prysm/:/data -p 12000:12000/udp -p 13000:13000 gcr.io/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain:latest --datadir=/data --medalla --rpc-host=0.0.0.0 `\r\n\r\n- Start validator, attach it to the docker network and have it connect to beacon-chain via the docker network\r\n`docker run --name validator --network medalla -v e:/prysm/:/data gcr.io/prysmaticlabs/prysm/validator:latest --keystore-path=/data --datadir=/data --password=yourPassword --medalla --beacon-rpc-provider=beacon-chain:4000 `\r\n \r\n",
